--- "Andrey G. Grozin" <A.G.Grozin@inp.nsk.su> wrote:

> I agree that it would be much better to replace clef by the de-facto 
> standard, readline. But... readline is GPL (not LGPL, and on
> purpose).  This will make axiom+readline to be distributable only
> under GPL.  (Absolutely OK for me, but some people may not like
this).

This is inherent in using GCL itself, actually - IIRC there are some
fairly non-trivial parts of GCL that are GPL and not LGPL.  I don't
know if Axiom can run without them or not.

Working on SBCL should allow for a complete "freer than GPL"
distribution, if that's important.  Personally I prefer that for
simplicity.  However, I am not particularly disturbed by the GPL GCL
either. 

linedit is under MIT style license, so a spruced up version of that
would make the solution Lisp only and avoid any issues at all. 
Unfortunately it uses UFFI at the moment - the ideal case would be to
have it not need any FFI, but if that is not possible I think CFFI is
the logial target.

Anyway, I don't think it's a pressing issue right now.

Cheers,
CY


       
